The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a general class of problems that can be formulated as linear programs with non-negative coefficients. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions specific problems such as multicommodity network flow, set cover, bin-packing, knapsack, scheduling problems, minimum-weight triangulation, which are commonly studied in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the mention of parallel algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
